congruence multiplication,"If a ≡ b mod m and c ≡ d mod m, then a*c ≡ b*d mod m","prove:
    exist_prop k Z st mod(a, b Z, m N_pos):
        a - b = k * m

    claim:
        foall a, b, c, d Z, m N_pos:
            $mod(a, b, m)
            $mod(c, d, m)
            =>:
                $mod(a * c, b * d, m)
        prove:
            have k_1 st $mod(a, b, m)
            have k_2 st $mod(c, d, m)
            a - b = k_1 * m
            c - d = k_2 * m
            a - b + b = k_1 * m + b
            c - d + d = k_2 * m + d
            a = k_1 * m + b
            c = k_2 * m + d
            =:
                a * c - b * d
                (k_1 * m + b) * (k_2 * m + d) - b * d
                k_1 * k_2 * m^2 + (k_1 * d + k_2 * b) * m
                (k_1 * k_2 * m + k_1 * d + k_2 * b) * m
            let k Z: k = k_1 * k_2 * m + k_1 * d + k_2 * b
            exist k st $mod(a * c, b * d, m)
            $mod(a * c, b * d, m)
"